CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 15, 1958, pg. 16, reads: " THE ARTIST AUTOGRAPHS - Philippa Duke Schuyler autographs programs for some of her young admirers following the splendid concert Monday night at Carnegie Hall. A delighted, enthusiastic audience brought the young pianist back for several encores at the end of the concert.  Grace Memorial Presbyterian Church members, headed by Mrs. Daisy E. Lampkin, sponsored the concert, one of several affairs celebrating the 90th anniversary of the church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Philippa Duke Schuyler wearing floral dress and holding bouquet, signing autograph for girl holding notebook, in Carnegie Music Hall
